[{"location":"dev.html#Developer-Guide","page":"Developer Guide","title":"Developer Guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started.html#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started.html#Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"To install the package run one of the following commands in the Julia REPL.","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"Using SSH:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"git@git.rwth-aachen.de:nick1/XIMC-jl.git\")","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"Using HTTPS:","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://git.rwth-aachen.de/nick1/XIMC-jl.git\")","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html#Dependencies","page":"Getting Started","title":"Dependencies","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"For the package to work the XIMC library provided by Standa [https://libximc.xisupport.com/doc-en/index.html] needs to be installed on your machine. Make sure that the installation directory is added to the enviroment variable, such that the linker can find the library (E.g. for windows the path has to be added to the PATH variable).","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html#Example-usage","page":"Getting Started","title":"Example usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"A simple example on how to use the Package. Connecting to the motor and moving it.","category":"page"},{"location":"getting_started.html","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"using XIMC\n\n# Connect to motor with URI \"Big Chungus\"\nD = requestDevices(\"Big Chungus\")\n\n# Move the motor to position: 1000 steps and 0 micro steps\n# and wait for it stop\ncommandMove(D, 1000, 0)\ncommandWaitForStop(D)\n\n# Close the connection\ncloseDevice(D)","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html#User-Guide","page":"User guide","title":"User Guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html#Structs","page":"User guide","title":"Structs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"DeviceId\nPosition","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.DeviceId","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.DeviceId","text":"DeviceId = device_t\n\nStores the id of a motor as int\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.Position","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.Position","text":"Position = get_position_t\n\nStores the position of a motor.\n\nFields\n\nPosition::Cint: The step of the motor\nuPosition::Cint The micro step of the motor\nEncPosition::long_t The encoder position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"user.html#Functions","page":"User guide","title":"Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html#Control","page":"User guide","title":"Control","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"Functions to control the motors.","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"requestDevices\ncloseDevice\ncloseDevices\ngetPosition\ngetPosition!\ngetSpeed\nsetSpeed\ncommandMove\ncommandWaitForStop","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.requestDevices","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.requestDevices","text":"requestDevices(address, stagenames...)\n\nOpen the connection to motors with given identifiers stagenames. If successful, returns a Vector{DeviceId} of given motors in the same order.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.closeDevice","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.closeDevice","text":"closeDevice(device::DeviceId)\n\nClose the connection to the motor.\n\n\n\n\n\ncloseDevice(device::DeviceId)\n\nClose the connection to multiple motors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.closeDevices","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.closeDevices","text":"const closeDevices(devices::Vector{DeviceId}) = closeDevice.(devices)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.getPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.getPosition","text":"getPosition(device::DeviceId)\n\nReturn the current position of specified motor in steps.\n\n\n\n\n\ngetPosition(devices::Vector{DeviceId}; fmt::Type=Matrix)\n\nReturn the current position of multiple motors.\n\nThe return type can be given by fmt:\n\nMatrix: (#devices, 3)-Matrix   ,where each row corresponds to the motor in devices and contains   [Position, uPosition, EncPosition]\nVector: Vector of Tuple{Int,Int} of length #devices, where the tuple is   (Position, uPosition)\n\nThe default is Matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\ngetPosition(devices::DeviceId...; fmt::Type=Matrix)\n\n\n\n\n\nfunction getPosition(devices::Vector{DeviceId},\n    cal::Dict{String,Tuple{Symbol,Float64}};\n    outputunit=:m)\n    \nReturn the position in given unit instead of steps.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.getPosition!","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.getPosition!","text":"getPosition!(pos::Position, device::DeviceId)\n\nStore the current position of specified motor into pos.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.getSpeed","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.getSpeed","text":"getSpeed(device::DeviceId)\n\nReturns a tuple (Speed, uSpeed) of the speed in steps/s.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.setSpeed","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.setSpeed","text":"setSpeed(device::DeviceId,speed::Integer; info=false)\n\nSet the speed of the motor in steps/s.\n\n\n\n\n\nsetSpeed(device::DeviceId,speed::Integer, uSpeed::Integer; info=false)\n\nSet the speed of the motor in steps/s and (micro steps)/s.\n\n\n\n\n\nsetSpeed(device::Vector{DeviceId}, speed::Integer; info=false)\n\nSet the speed of multiple motors in steps/s.\n\n\n\n\n\nsetSpeed(device::Vector{DeviceId}, speed::Integer; info=false)\n\nSet the speed of multiple motors in steps/s and (micro steps)/s.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.commandMove","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.commandMove","text":"commandMove(device::DeviceId, pos::Real, upos::Real; info=false)\n\nMove the motor to the Position given by the steps pos and micro steps upos. If info=true the return is printed to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandMove(device::DeviceId,pos::Position; info=false)\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandMove(devices::Vector{DeviceId},positions::Vector{Tuple{Int,Int}})\n\nMove multiple motors to the given positions.\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandMove(devices::Vector{DeviceId},positions::Matrix{Int32})\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandMove(device::DeviceId,x::Real,cal::Dict{String,Tuple{Symbol,Float64}}; info=false,inputunit=:mm)\n\nMove the motor using specified unit instead of steps.\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandMove(devices::Vector{DeviceId},x::Vector{<:Real},cal::Dict{String,Tuple{Symbol,Float64}}; info=false,inputunit=:mm)\n\nMove multiplied motors using specified unit instead of steps.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.commandWaitForStop","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.commandWaitForStop","text":"commandWaitForStop(device::DeviceId; interval::UInt32=0x00000a,info::Bool=false)\n\nWaiting for the specified motor to stop moving.\n\ninterval specifies how many milliseconds the function waits to check again   whether the motor is still moving.\n\n\n\n\n\ncommandWaitForStop(devices::Vector{DeviceId}; interval::UInt32=0x00000a,info::Bool=false)\n\nWaiting for multiple motors to stop moving.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Information","page":"User guide","title":"Information","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"Functions which print out information to the console.","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"infoXIMC\ninfoDevice\ninfoMoveSettings\ninfoPosition\ninfoSerial\ninfoSpeed\ninfoStage\ninfoStatus","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoXIMC","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoXIMC","text":"infoXIMC()\n\nPrints and returns the current version number of the XIMC library.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoDevice","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoDevice","text":"infoDevice(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint basic information about the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoMoveSettings","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoMoveSettings","text":"infoMoveSettings(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint move settings of the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoPosition","text":"infoPosition(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint position of the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoSerial","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoSerial","text":"infoSerial(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint serial number of the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoSpeed","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoSpeed","text":"infoSpeed(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint speed settings of the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoStage","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoStage","text":"infoStage(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint stage information about the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.infoStatus","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.infoStatus","text":"infoStatus(device::DeviceId)\n\nPrint status information about the motor to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Miscellaneous","page":"User guide","title":"Miscellaneous","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"isSamePosition\nisGreaterEqPosition\nisSmallerEqPosition\nisGreaterPosition\nisSmallerPosition\n==\n>=\n<=\n>\n<","category":"page"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.isSamePosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.isSamePosition","text":"isSamePosition(x::Position, y::Position)\n\nReturns wether x and y are the same Position.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.isGreaterEqPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.isGreaterEqPosition","text":"isGreaterEqPosition(x::Position, y::Position)\n\nReturns x >= y. Note, that you can use the operator itself (eg. x >= y).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.isSmallerEqPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.isSmallerEqPosition","text":"isSmallerEqPosition(x::Position, y::Position)\n\nReturns x <= y. Note, that you can use the operator itself (eg. x <= y).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.isGreaterPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.isGreaterPosition","text":"isGreaterPosition(x::Position, y::Position)\n\nReturns x > y. Note, that you can use the operator itself (eg. x > y).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Main.XIMC.isSmallerPosition","page":"User guide","title":"Main.XIMC.isSmallerPosition","text":"isSmallerPosition(x::Position, y::Position)\n\nReturns x < y. Note, that you can use the operator itself (eg. x < y).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Base.:==","page":"User guide","title":"Base.:==","text":"const ==(x::Position, y::Position) = isSamePosition(x, y)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Base.:>=","page":"User guide","title":"Base.:>=","text":"const >=(x::Position, y::Position) = isGreaterEqPosition(x, y)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Base.:<=","page":"User guide","title":"Base.:<=","text":"const <=(x::Position, y::Position) = isSmallerEqPosition(x, y)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Base.:>","page":"User guide","title":"Base.:>","text":"const >(x::Position, y::Position) = isGreaterPosition(x, y)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Base.:<","page":"User guide","title":"Base.:<","text":"const <(x::Position, y::Position) = isSmallerPosition(x, y)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"user.html#Index","page":"User guide","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"user.html","page":"User guide","title":"User guide","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#XIMC-(WIP)","page":"About","title":"XIMC (WIP)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"Julia wrapper for XIMC motor control package by Standa (www.standa.lt).   The standard wrapper has been expanded for ease of use and to conform more to Julian standards.  ","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"This module was created as part of the MADMAX project at RWTH Aachen. The functionality is suited to the needs of one project and therefore offers not yet the full functionality possible.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"This documentation gives a overview over the package and its usage. For a quick start see Getting Started.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Contents","page":"About","title":"Contents","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Contact","page":"About","title":"Contact","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"The XIMC julia wrapper was developed by","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"About","title":"About","text":"Bergermann, Dominik dominik.bergermann@rwth-aachen.de\nMichaelis, Nick nick.michaelis@rwth-aachen.de","category":"page"}]
